[P1_1_1_TrainingText]
Training_0053L=The Stealth Meter in the bottom right hand corner indicates how well you are lit.
Training_0090L=When the tab is at the right side of the meter, you are well lit. When the tab is at the left side of the meter, you are practically invisible.
Training_0091L=The Stealth Meter in the bottom right hand corner indicates how well you are lit.
Training_0108L=(null)
Training_0055L=The Objective Bar at the bottom of your HUD keeps you informed of your current Objectives.
Training_0108L=(null)
Training_0051L=When a small flashing envelope appears above your OPSAT, a new goal or a new note is available. Press the OPSAT key (F1) / (Controller: Back) to open it and read the note.
Goal_0023L=Infiltrate the embassy.
Goal_0024L=Infiltrate the embassy.
Training_0004L=Press the Jump key (Shift) / (Controller: Y) at the base of a ledge to grab onto it.
Training_0005L=Move the mouse / (Controller: RS) to look around.
Training_0006L=To climb a ladder, simply move or jump towards it.
Training_0007L=To use a zip line, stand under it and press the Jump key (Shift) / (Controller: Y) to jump and grab it.
Training_0008L=To grab a beam or a horizontal pipe, stand under it and press the Jump key (Shift) / (Controller: Y). You can move hand-over-hand along it.
Training_0009L=While hanging on a pipe, press the Jump key (Shift) / (Controller: Y) to bring your legs up. This will decrease your visibility and enable you to pass over obstacles.
Training_0111L=(null)
Training_0085L=While you are holding a horizontal pipe with your legs up, press Equip key (E) / (Controller: X) to hang by your legs and draw your weapon.
Training_0112L=(null)
Training_0100L=While hanging from a pipe, beam, or ledge, press the Crouch key (C) / (Controller: B) to drop down.
Training_0113L=(null)
Training_0010L=To open a door, press the Interaction key (Space) / (Controller: A) when the interaction window appears.
Note_0057L=To avoid being surprised, use the optic cable to check a room before entering it.
Training_0087L=You can pick a lock using a lock pick. In front of the door press the Interaction key (Space) / (Controller: A) and select lock pick in the interaction window to begin picking the lock.
Training_0125L=To release a pin, you must press the correct movement key (W or S or A or D by default) / (Controller: LS).Once you hear and see the pin begin to move, press the same key repeatedly until it is released. Repeat until all pins are released.
Training_0011L=You can pick a lock using a lock pick. In front of the door press the Interaction key (Space) / (Controller: A) and select lock pick in the interaction window to begin picking the lock.
Training_0012L=To release a pin, you must press the correct movement key (W or S or A or D by default) / (Controller: LS).Once you hear and see the pin begin to move, press the same key repeatedly until it is released. Repeat until all pins are released.
Training_0014L=To climb a pipe or a beam, simply move or jump towards it.
Training_0016L=To crouch, press the Crouch key (C) / (Controller: B). You will make much less noise while crouched and moving slowly.
Note_0105L=You will also perform a Quiet Landing if you drop from a height while crouched.
Training_0088L=To crouch, press the Crouch key (C) / (Controller: B). You will make much less noise while crouched and moving slowly.
Training_0089L=You will also perform a Quiet Landing if you drop from a height while crouched.
Training_0114L=(null)
Training_0017L=To put your back to a wall, face the wall and press (Q) / (Controller: LS Press). You will peek when you reach a corner.
Note_0106L=The SWAT Turn is a highly trained Special Forces movement that makes you almost invisible.
Training_0018L=While you are peeking at an open door or a small corridor, press the Action key (Space) / (Controller: A) to perform a SWAT turn.
Training_0086L=While you are peeking at an open door or a small corridor, press the Action key (Space) / (Controller: A) to perform a SWAT turn.
Training_0098L=The SWAT Turn is a highly trained Special Forces movement that makes you almost invisible.
Training_0124L=(null)
Note_0061L=When equipped with the pistol, press the Alternate Fire key (right mouse button) / (Controller: LT) to activate the laser targeting. When the laser targeting is activated, your aiming is more precise, but the red dot can be seen by the enemies.
Note_0063L=Press (Tab) / (Controller: D-Pad Down) to select an object you can throw. While peeking, press the Equip key (E) / (Controller: X) to equip the object and press the Fire key (left mouse button) / (Controller: RT) to throw it. While the object is equipped, you can adjust throwing length by pressing the Alternate Fire key (right mouse button) / (Controller: LT).
Training_0019L=You will need to shoot the light out to pass unnoticed. From back to wall, go to the peeking position by moving towards the edge of the wall.
Training_0118L=Press the Equip key (E) / (Controller: X) to draw the pistol. When equipped with a weapon, press the Fire key (left mouse button) / (Controller: RT) to shoot.
Training_0121L=Press the Equip key (E) / (Controller: X) to draw the pistol. When equipped with a weapon, press the Fire key (left mouse button) / (Controller: RT) to shoot.
Training_0123L=(null)
Training_0022L=To equip your Night Vision Goggles, simply press (2) / (Controller: D-Pad Left). To return to normal vision, press (2) / (Controller: D-Pad Left) again.
Training_0075L=You will need to shoot the light to pass unnoticed. From back to wall, go to the peeking position and press the Equip key (E) / (Controller: B) to draw the pistol. When equipped with a weapon, press the Fire key (left mouse button) / (Controller: RT) to shoot.
Training_0076L=During the game, press the Inventory key (Ctrl) / (Controller: RB) to access the quick inventory.
Note_0103L=Use the mouse or arrows to select an item. To use the item, press the Fire key (left mouse button) / (Controller: RT).
Training_0104L=During the game, press the Inventory key (Ctrl) / (Controller: RB) to access the quick inventory.
Training_0107L=Use the mouse or arrows to select an item. To use the item, press the Fire key (left mouse button) / (Controller: RT).
Training_0102L=To access the binoculars, press the Zoom key (middle mouse button) / (Controller: RS Press).
Training_0023L=Approach your opponent quietly from behind and press the Interaction key (Space) / (Controller: A) to grab him.
Training_0067L=(null)
Training_0024L=If the character has any useful information, the Interrogate interaction will appear. Select this interaction to force the character to talk.
Training_0068L=(null)
Training_0025L=After you get the information you need, press the Fire key (left mouse button) / (Controller: RT) to knock out and release your opponent.
Training_0078L=Approach your opponent quietly from behind and press the Interaction key (Space) / (Controller: A) to grab him.
Training_0079L=If the character has any useful information, the Interrogate interaction will appear. Select this interaction to force the character to talk.
Training_0080L=After you get the information you need, press the Fire key (left mouse button) / (Controller: RT) to knock out and release your opponent.
Training_0026L=Land mines can only be detected in thermal vision.
Training_0092L=To equip your thermal Vision Goggles, simply press (3) / (Controller: D-Pad Right).
Training_0093L=To return to normal vision, press (3) / (Controller: D-Pad Right) again.
Training_0094L=To equip your thermal Vision Goggles, simply press (3) / (Controller: D-Pad Right).
Training_0066L=(null)
Training_0027L=When in a narrow passage, you can perform a split jump by standing next to a wall and pressing the Jump key (Shift) / (Controller: Y). At the top of the jump, press the Jump key (Shift) / (Controller: Y) again to complete the maneuver.
Training_0038L=(null)
Training_0028L=From a half split jump, you can reach a position above yourself. Face the higher position by moving left or right, then press the Jump key (Shift) / (Controller: Y) to reach it.
Training_0072L=When in a narrow passage, you can perform a split jump by standing next to a wall and pressing the Jump key (Shift). At the top of the jump, press the Jump key (Shift) / (Controller: Y) again to complete the maneuver.
Training_0099L=From a half split jump, you can reach a position above yourself. Face the higher position by moving left or right, then press the Jump key (Shift) / (Controller: Y) to reach it.
Training_0116L=(null)
Training_0101L=You can whistle using the Whistle key (V) / (Controller: LB). If a guard hears this, he will investigate the sound.
Training_0029L=You will be much quieter while crouched and moving slowly. You will also perform a Quiet Landing if you drop from a height while crouched.
Training_0030L=Approach your opponent quietly from behind and press the Interaction key (Space) / (Controller: A) to grab him.
Training_0040L=(null)
Training_0031L=Stand over the fallen enemy, press the Interaction key (Space) / (Controller: A) and select the Body interaction. Carry the body to somewhere dark and out of the way, then press the Interaction key (Space) / (Controller: A) to drop him. 
Note_0084L=When you drop a body your stealth meter will flash twice indicating that the body is well hidden in the dark at the time you drop it.
Training_0074L=Stand over the fallen enemy, press the Interaction key (Space) / (Controller: A) and select the Body interaction. Carry the body to somewhere dark and out of the way, then press the Interaction key (Space) / (Controller: A) to drop him. 
Training_0035L=(null)

